Makes the LLVM toolchain binaries (clang, lld, llvm-*) LOAD and run on Windows
XP/2000. lib/Support's Windows code statically imports functions that don't
exist before Vista/Win7; a static import of a missing function makes the whole
.exe fail to start. Each is resolved dynamically via GetProcAddress (as LLVM
already does for PrefetchVirtualMemory / SetThreadInformation), with a fallback:

  Path.inc:
    - GetFinalPathNameByHandleW (Vista): realPathFromHandle fails soft.
    - SetFileInformationByHandle (Vista): rename() uses MoveFileExW by path.
    - SHGetKnownFolderPath (Vista): falls back to SHGetFolderPathW + CSIDL.
    - SHCreateItemFromIDList (Vista): remove_directories falls back to the
      classic SHFileOperationW.
  Threading.inc:
    - GetLogicalProcessorInformationEx / Get|SetThreadGroupAffinity /
      GetProcessGroupAffinity (Win7): collapse to a single GetSystemInfo group.
  Memory.inc:
    - GetLargePageMinimum (Vista): returns 0 -> large pages stay disabled.

The psapi imports (K32EnumProcessModules / K32GetProcessMemoryInfo) are handled
separately by building with -DPSAPI_VERSION=1 (routes them to psapi.dll), not by
this patch.

